cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents an algorithm for verifying safety properties of software systems, which involves logical reasoning and model checking. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm in Cubicle, a model checker for array-based systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper focuses on verifying safety properties of software systems, which is a key concern in software engineering. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with reachability graphs and counter-example approximation, which are concepts related to formal languages and automata theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper presents an algorithm for building an abstract reachability graph, which involves data structures and algorithms.
